section.p:
A sample space is the set of all possible outcomes for a random process.  We will usually denote the sample space by S.  An event is any possible outcome.  For example, we can have the following events for rolling a pair of dice,

                A \amp = \{ \text{rolling a 7}\}
                B \amp = \{ \text{rolling an even number}\}
                C \amp = \{ \text{rolling a 17}\}.

        We will designate the probability of an event A by P(A).
